==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Black friar
<hw>Black" fri`ar</hw></mhw>
<pr>(bl⟦acr⟧k"fr⟦imac⟧`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>. <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A friar of
the Dominican order, so named because wearing the black mantle of the
Dominicans; -- called also <altname>predicant</altname> and
<altname>preaching friar</altname>; in France,
<altname>Jacobin</altname>. Also, sometimes, a Benedictine.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Dominican.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Black Friday</ent>⟦br⟧
